text.section:
When the Administration receives a notice of conviction from a party state to the Driver License Compact under Subtitle 7 of this title, the Administration may not assess points against an individual, except upon receipt of reports of the following convictions:
Manslaughter or negligent homicide resulting from the operation of a motor vehicle;
Driving a motor vehicle while under the influence of intoxicating liquor or a narcotic drug, while intoxicated per se, or while under the influence of any other drug to a degree that renders the driver incapable of safely driving a motor vehicle;
Any felony in the commission of which a motor vehicle is used; or
Failure to stop and render aid in the event of a motor vehicle accident resulting in the death or personal injury of another.
